Zall Group Ltd. Key Developments

Zall Group Ltd. Announces Executive Changes
Jun 28 17
The Board of Zall Group Ltd. announced that, with effect from 28 June 2017: Mr. Wei Zhe has been re-designated from an independent non-executive Director to an executive Director and has resigned as the chairman of the Remuneration Committee and a member of the Audit Committee and Nomination Committee; Mr. Zhu Zhengfu has been appointed as the chairman of the Remuneration Committee and a member of the Audit Committee; and Mr. Cheung Ka Fai has been appointed as a member of the Nomination Committee.


Zall Group Ltd., Annual General Meeting, May 18, 2017
Apr 13 17
Zall Group Ltd., Annual General Meeting, May 18, 2017, at 10:30 China Standard Time. Location: Suite 2101, 21/F Two Exchange Square, Central Hong Kong Agenda: To receive, consider and adopt the audited consolidated financial statements and the reports of the directors of the Company (the "Directors") and the auditors of the company for the year ended 31 December 2016; to re-elect Mr. Cui Jinfeng and Mr. Peng Chi as executive Directors; Mr. Cheung Ka Fai as independent non-executive Director; and Mr. Zhu Zhengfu as independent non-executive Director; to authorise the board of Directors to fix the Directors remuneration; to re-appoint KPMG as Auditors and authorise the Board to fix their remuneration; to grant a general mandate to the Directors to allot, issue and deal with shares of the company not exceeding 20% of the total number of Shares in issue as at the date of passing this resolution; to grant a general mandate to the Directors to buy back shares not exceeding 10% of the total number of Shares in issue as at the date of passing this resolution; and to consider conditional upon the passing of resolutions nos. 5 and 6.


Zall Group Ltd. Announces Audited Consolidated Cash Flow Results for the Year Ended December 31, 2016
Apr 13 17
Zall Group Ltd. announced audited consolidated cash flow results for the year ended December 31, 2016. For the year, the company announced net cash used in operating activities was RMB 289,388,000 compared to RMB 1,440,112,000 for the same period a year ago.


